little suitcases.

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:31.410
So imagine carrying
like two backpacks

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:35.250
worth of your belongings
and going to another country

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:36.690
to start over.

00:01:36.690 --> 00:01:42.270
And so what did we have but the
flavors that my parents wanted

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:42.990
to recreate.

00:01:42.990 --> 00:01:46.530
And they were people in
their forties with five kids.

00:01:46.530 --> 00:01:50.370
And so, you know, we weren't
living near a Pho shop.

00:01:50.370 --> 00:01:53.010
We couldn't walk out and
get Pho like we used to.

00:01:53.010 --> 00:01:57.060
So they ended up making a
lot of the food at home.

00:01:57.060 --> 00:01:59.940
And initially we
had to cook a lot

00:01:59.940 --> 00:02:04.650
from an American supermarket,
which back in 1979--

00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:07.710
and some of you may be
old enough to remember--

00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:09.810
it was really sad.

00:02:09.810 --> 00:02:14.520
Soy sauce, bad rice,
yucky vegetables.

00:02:14.520 --> 00:02:16.470
A lot of that has changed.

00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:19.560
And with "The Pho Cookbook,"
because a lot of people

00:02:19.560 --> 00:02:20.820
sense it's like, oh!

00:02:20.820 --> 00:02:22.020
I can't make pho.

00:02:22.020 --> 00:02:25.196
I've had people tell
me that it takes hours!

00:02:25.196 --> 00:02:26.820
I've even had Vietnamese
people tell me

00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:28.500
that their parents
tell them, oh my God!

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:31.750
It takes like an
overnight simmer.

00:02:31.750 --> 00:02:36.540
And pho shop owners will say,
I brewed this pho for 18 hours.

00:02:36.540 --> 00:02:41.010
Well, when you're making pho at
home for as few as two people

00:02:41.010 --> 00:02:44.460
or up to eight people,
you can really, really

00:02:44.460 --> 00:02:47.250
spend a lot less time, because
you're small batching it.

00:02:47.250 --> 00:02:50.220
You're making
artisanal pho at home.

00:02:50.220 --> 00:02:53.130
So you don't have to
spend that much time.

00:02:53.130 --> 00:02:55.410
So when you work your
way through the book,

00:02:55.410 --> 00:02:57.690
you'll notice that
at the front part

00:02:57.690 --> 00:02:59.940
there is this thing
called a pho manual.

00:02:59.940 --> 00:03:04.650
And it explains like 99% of
what I know about making pho.

00:03:04.650 --> 00:03:08.070
And the extra 1% is very
boring and distracting.

00:03:08.070 --> 00:03:10.650
So I left that out.

00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:12.180
For example, like
one man told me

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:14.969
he had to scrape the bones
off until his knuckles bled

00:03:14.969 --> 00:03:15.510
or something.

00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:19.174
And I was like, I'm not
putting that in the book.

00:03:19.174 --> 00:03:21.090
I was just like, he said
it's a waste of time.

00:03:21.090 --> 00:03:22.050
And I thought, well, yeah.

00:03:22.050 --> 00:03:22.620
I think so.

00:03:25.770 --> 00:03:28.020
And then after the
pho manual, there's

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:29.850
