365 broth is really good.

00:03:59.130 --> 00:04:01.950
You want sort of a
higher sodium broth.

00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:04.110
And so there are three
different recipes.

00:04:04.110 --> 00:04:08.310
40 minutes, with grocery stores
ingredients like this, and then

00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:10.560
with like Annie Chun noodles--

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:13.890
if you're shopping at a regular
market, it's very good--

00:04:13.890 --> 00:04:14.790
you can have pho.

00:04:14.790 --> 00:04:17.240
Chicken, vegetable, or beef.

00:04:17.240 --> 00:04:20.370
There is another
method of making pho

00:04:20.370 --> 00:04:21.510
using a pressure cooker.

00:04:21.510 --> 00:04:23.670
How many of you own
pressure cookers?

00:04:23.670 --> 00:04:24.570
The instant pot.

00:04:24.570 --> 00:04:25.952
How many are you
instant potters?

00:04:28.850 --> 00:04:31.896
So you can spend like
an hour and a half,

00:04:31.896 --> 00:04:33.770
if you're using an
instant pot, please reduce

00:04:33.770 --> 00:04:35.490
the amount of water by one cup.

00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:35.990
OK?

00:04:35.990 --> 00:04:39.470
Just saying that,
because the instant pot

00:04:39.470 --> 00:04:43.100
has this maximum fill
line, as you know.

00:04:43.100 --> 00:04:44.540
And you can go up to that point.

00:04:44.540 --> 00:04:49.500
And it also retains pressure
for a very, very long time.

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:53.020
So you can kind of save
yourself a little time.

00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:54.350
And it's not venting.

00:04:54.350 --> 00:04:56.330
So you should get
the same quantity

00:04:56.330 --> 00:04:58.580
with one cup less water.

00:04:58.580 --> 00:05:00.830
Just saying.

00:05:00.830 --> 00:05:03.920
If you're using something like
a pressure cooker to make pho,

00:05:03.920 --> 00:05:07.580
you can do it in an hour and
a half from beginning to end.

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:13.280
And you can also then
freeze your broth.

00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:14.900
And there are
instructions on how

00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:18.260
