00:56:33.040 --> 00:56:35.980
ANDREA NGUYEN: Well, the way
that I prepare tofu in the book

00:56:35.980 --> 00:56:37.030
is very simple.

00:56:37.030 --> 00:56:43.180
So I get a block
of extra-firm tofu.

00:56:43.180 --> 00:56:48.790
So that's the tofu that is
sold in a tub with water--

00:56:48.790 --> 00:56:51.650
with a moat of water around it.

00:56:51.650 --> 00:56:56.280
And so I'll slice the tofu.

00:56:56.280 --> 00:57:00.970
The tofu that Google
gets is restaurant size.

00:57:00.970 --> 00:57:04.150
So it's a little bit
different than what we see.

00:57:04.150 --> 00:57:05.650
But I get the tofu.

00:57:05.650 --> 00:57:08.680
And I'll cut it into
pieces about this size.

00:57:08.680 --> 00:57:11.440
And then I put it into
a nonstick skillet

00:57:11.440 --> 00:57:14.640
with a little bit of soy sauce.

00:57:14.640 --> 00:57:16.810
In the book, the recipe
is called pan-seared tofu.

00:57:16.810 --> 00:57:20.295
And it's one of my favorite ways
of making a grab and go tofu.

00:57:20.295 --> 00:57:22.240
So you put your tofu in there.

00:57:22.240 --> 00:57:25.360
No need to do that draining
business, all righty?

00:57:25.360 --> 00:57:29.500
Because in the skillet it
will release its liquid.

00:57:29.500 --> 00:57:32.740
Add soy sauce, turn
the tofu a few times.

00:57:32.740 --> 00:57:37.330
And then you turn on your
heat to around medium or so.

00:57:37.330 --> 00:57:41.399
The tofu then will release
its natural liquid.

00:57:41.399 --> 00:57:42.940
So it's draining
right there for you.

00:57:42.940 --> 00:57:45.490
It's then going to
get coated and pick up

00:57:45.490 --> 00:57:50.270
some flavor from the soy sauce.

00:57:50.270 --> 00:57:53.800
And then once that the
tofu looks kind of dryish,

00:57:53.800 --> 00:57:55.990
add a little bit of oil.

00:57:55.990 --> 00:57:59.230
And then you're going to
let that outer coating kind

00:57:59.230 --> 00:58:01.300
of sear and fry a little bit.

00:58:01.300 --> 00:58:03.170
And then once that's done--

00:58:03.170 --> 00:58:06.100
and total cooking time is like
10 minutes-- you are home.

00:58:06.100 --> 00:58:08.290
And then you just cool it.

00:58:08.290 --> 00:58:09.940
And I keep that in the fridge.

00:58:09.940 --> 00:58:12.400
And it lasts for days.

00:58:12.400 --> 00:58:14.140
